# Frontend configuration (Vite) — optional.
#
# In local dev, the Vite dev server proxies /api → http://localhost:8000
# (see vite.config.ts), so you don't need to set anything.
#
# In production, the recommended setup leaves this UNSET and lets vercel.json
# proxy /api/* to the Railway backend (no CORS, no rebuild when the backend
# URL changes). Alternatively, point the frontend straight at the backend by
# setting the origin below (the backend's CORS_ORIGINS must then include the
# frontend domain):
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-railway-backend.up.railway.app
